Description: Fragment of wall of probably East Greek pottery vessel; inside smoothed, suggesting it is an open vase. Very worn glaze and one add red line preserved on outside. Inscription on outside.
Curator's comments: There is probably enough mica in the clay to rule out a Corinthian origin.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GS.332)
